 a subgroup of closely related languages rather than a single language. The central topics discussed in the book are: Slavic impact on Romani phonetics and phonology, morphology and syntax; forms and functions of Slavic verbal prefixes in Romani; Slavic impact on the Romani lexicon; Romani elements in the nonstandard lexicon of the Slavic languages; writing Romani with ‘Slavic’ alphabets.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aLanguages in contactzEurope. 0aRomani languagexForeign words and phrases. 0aRomani language. 0aSlavic languagesxForeign words and phrases. 0aSlavic languagesxInfluence on Romani. 0aSlavic languages. 4aRomani. 4aSlavisch. 4aSprachkontakt. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aLanguage Contact.  aRomani.  aSlavic.0 cEPUBz97831107562410 cprintz978311075604340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311075617340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110756173423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110756173/original  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK